The paper deals with aligning CAD models to 3D scans, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection and dense correspondence prediction. Additionally, the paper involves geometric reasoning (GR) to align the CAD models to the scans. The use of a differentiable Procrustes alignment and a fully-convolutional approach suggests the involvement of robotics (RO) and machine learning (LG) techniques. Finally, the end-to-end nature of the approach suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques.
